definition:
δείκνυμι, δεικνύω (see Bl., § 23, 1; Veitch, see word), 
 [in LXX chiefly for רָאָה hi. ;] 
to show, with accusative of thing(s) (of person(s)), dative of person(s); 
   (a) to show, exhibit: Mat.4:8 8:4, Mrk.1:44 14:15, Luk.4:5 5:14 20:24 22:12 24:40, Jhn.2:18 5:20 10:32; 20:20 Act.7:3" (LXX), 1Ti.6:15, Rev.17:1 21:9, 10 22:1, 8, pass., Heb.8:5 (LXX); 
   (b) to make known: Mat.16:21, Jhn.14:8, 9, Act.10:28, 1Co.12:31, Rev.1:1 4:1 22:6; 
   (with) to prove: Jas.2:18 3:13.†
 (AS)
